Hello. We’re Virgin Australia. We’re the airline that’s always done things a
little different. Our way. The Virgin way. We’re on a mission to make flying
better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are
passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a
focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who
values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.

** What you’ll be doing **

This newly created Data Engineer role will be responsible for ingesting data
into our modern data platform, assembling large, complex datasets and
providing frameworks and services for operating on that data, enabling the
business to deliver on reporting, dashboarding, marketing and advanced
analytics initiatives.

This role will be reporting to the Data Platform Lead, working within a team
of data engineers, supported by data analysts and a Data Platform Architect.

  * Develop robust data pipelines and processes in Databricks, making critical business data available to other teams 
  * Manage and optimise data pipelines for performance, scalability, reliability and cost efficiency. 
  * Ingest data into our modern data platform, assemble large, complex datasets, and provide frameworks and services for operating on that data 
  * Identify, design, and implement internal process improvements, such as automating manual processes and optimizing data delivery 
  * Collaborate with stakeholders to understand their data requirements and provide effective solutions 

** You’ll be great in this role if you have… **

  * Extensive experience as a Data Engineer 
  * Understanding of data warehousing principles including data structures, database design, modelling, metadata, dependency and workload management 
  * Experience working with cloud-based, modern data platforms and Open Source Big Data tools 
  * Exposure to our current tech stack is desirable (Databricks, AWS, DBT with extensive experience with Spark, Python, SQL) 
  * Strong communication skills and the ability to work as part of a team or independently 

This is a ** Brisbane ** based role, however, we will also consider **
Melbourne ** candidates that are willing to commute periodically.

** What you’ll get from us **

We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and
conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to):

  * Discounted flights for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year) 
  * A flexible, hybrid work style. Work from home or the office, adapt your location to suit your style and needs 
  * One of Brisbane’s most admired head office locations, with South Bank train station, a supermarket, pharmacy, and lunch options downstairs plus a 5-minute walk to the Busway, a rooftop restaurant and onsite gym (with a low membership fee) and South Bank Parklands just across the road 
  * Discounts on travel insurance, lounge membership, car hire, accommodation, and experiences worldwide 
  * Cheaper hospitality, retail, technology, beauty and wellness services 
  * Free counselling and access to a wellbeing app to support your physical, mental, social and financial health 
  * ‘Dress for Your Day’ – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever makes you feel great for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you. 

** When everyone is included, everyone wins **

We’re all individuals. And we love that. That’s why we encourage applications
